## Counter — Trailing Underscore Convention

```cpp
private:
    int counter_;       // trailing _ = class attribute

void timerCallback() {
    RCLCPP_INFO(this->get_logger(), "Hello %d", counter_);
    counter_++;
}
```

> ⚠️ **`counter_` is never initialized** in your code. It happens to start at 0 because of zero-initialization of primitives in some contexts, but **you should explicitly initialize it** to avoid undefined behavior:
> ```cpp
> MyNode() : Node("cpp_test"), counter_(0) {   // ← initialize in member init list
>     // ...
> }
> ```

`RCLCPP_INFO` uses **printf-style formatting** (different from Python's `+ str(...)`):

```cpp
RCLCPP_INFO(this->get_logger(), "Hello %d", counter_);
//                              ↑       ↑   ↑
//                              format  int  argument
```

Common format specifiers: `%d` int, `%f` float, `%s` C string, `%.2f` float with 2 decimals.

